00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:30.040
 So you know, what is the mandala? The mandala is the whole sphere of purity.

00:03:30.040 --> 00:03:42.860
 You know, what's perfect, and clear, and spacious, kind of instead of a confused chaos, like what

00:03:42.860 --> 00:03:44.040
 is this?

00:03:44.040 --> 00:03:52.650
 The nature as it is, shining forth brilliantly. So the mandala, in that sense of that, is a whole

00:03:52.650 --> 00:03:53.040
 sphere

00:03:53.040 --> 00:04:04.040
 of enlightened activity and realization, and in essence, it's a way of symbolically representing

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:14.040
 everything that exists, be it on the existing to our mundane, you know, ordinary conception,

00:04:14.040 --> 00:04:23.040
 and then also all that as things are in the true nature state, the pure relative truth.

00:04:23.040 --> 00:04:35.530
 So the whole of everything, both in the kind of impure relative truth, as well as the pure relative

00:04:35.530 --> 00:04:37.040
 truth,

00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:45.040
 and of course the nature of both of those is the absolute truth of the great emptiness

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:54.040
 and indivisible with that, the great clarity, so that wisdom and compassion growing.

00:04:54.040 --> 00:04:59.040
 And then with our mandala practice, and in fact every part of our nundra,

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:09.040
 we have what's called the mandala of the absolute mandala of realization,

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:15.040
 the mandala that is our objects of refuge. So in that sense, it's here being embodied

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:23.040
 as Guru Padmasambhava, right, and all the refuge tree, embodiment of all the three jewels,

00:05:23.040 --> 00:05:30.040
 the three roots, the Buddha, Dharma, Sangha, Guru, Devas, Dakinis, Dharmapalas,

00:05:30.040 --> 00:05:39.570
 all the infinite realms of Buddhas and Bodhisattvas and Dakinis, Dharmapalas and lightened

00:05:39.570 --> 00:05:40.040
 activities,

00:05:40.040 --> 00:05:48.040
 in essence the realization of things as it is and the true nature as it is,

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:59.370
 and those who've realized it have perfected the path, or are well on the way in the Bhumis and

00:05:59.370 --> 00:06:00.040
 things,

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:11.040
 and so we are connecting with that in our practice, and so as part of that,

00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:16.040
 then we're making the mandala offering, like it says in the book here,

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:26.040
 is it the accumulation of merit. So in our path for ourselves, in our path of realization,

00:06:26.040 --> 00:06:31.040
 in our path of exploring the nature, there's two main things we're doing,

00:06:31.040 --> 00:06:37.040
 which we hear again and again, accumulating merit, accumulating wisdom,

00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:44.040
 and so this section of the nundra practice, which is the mandala offering,

00:06:44.040 --> 00:07:01.040
 is this very powerful, so simple but profound practice of accumulating merit and wisdom,

00:07:01.040 --> 00:07:09.040
 and then as aspiring Bodhisattvas, we're doing what's called actualizing our bodhicitta,

00:07:09.040 --> 00:07:15.040
 and I think we've all heard too, the paramitas, the six paramitas,

00:07:15.040 --> 00:07:21.040
 is another way of framing the accumulation of merit and wisdom,

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:33.040
 the practices that truly purify and awaken our pure potential to really actualize our bodhicitta,

00:07:33.040 --> 00:07:38.040
 and that all begins one way with the generosity practice,

00:07:38.040 --> 00:07:44.040
 and so the mandala offering is a big generosity practice,

00:07:44.040 --> 00:07:51.040
 but it's also, you know, we're getting things together, we're making the time,

00:07:51.040 --> 00:07:57.040
 we're gathering materials, we're doing the practice with our motivation,

00:07:57.040 --> 00:08:07.590
 and that's also the morality practice, and we're doing that with our patience and joyful effort,

00:08:07.590 --> 00:08:09.040
 concentration,

00:08:09.040 --> 00:08:16.040
 and then as we're doing that, developing more and more familiarity with the nature as it is,

00:08:16.040 --> 00:08:23.040
 which is developing our wisdom, they go hand in hand, like two wings, they say in the teachings,

00:08:23.040 --> 00:08:33.040
 developing wisdom and compassion through the practice of accumulating merit and wisdom,

